==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underload switch
<hw>Underload switch</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A switch which opens
a circuit when the current falls below a certain predetermined value,
used to protect certain types of motors from running at excessive speed
upon decrease of load.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>underlock</ent>⟦br⟧
